@* THE SLOT NAME BEATS THE SIBLING FILE (decision 168, register defect A6). SlotCard declares a
   `Slot` fragment and Slot.razor exists next door. Razor's codegen for this source is
   AddAttribute(…, "Slot", (RenderFragment)…) and OpenComponent<…Slot> appears NOWHERE.

   BEFORE #168 THIS EMITTED THE DECOY, at exit 0 -- sibling-file resolution ran first. Worse, it
   emitted the SAME BYTES as SlotClashCfact.razor, whose child declares ChildContent instead and
   where the decoy IS what Blazor instantiates: the emission was invariant to the declaration that
   decides the meaning. *@
<div id="wrap"><SlotCard><Slot><span id="body">@count</span></Slot></SlotCard><button id="inc" @onclick="Inc">inc</button></div>

@code {
    private int count = 0;
    void Inc() { count++; }
}
